article_id:180,category_name:Events,title_name:New Year's Tidings: Fortune from Afar Raid Event Now Open!,image_path:,message:<div>Up to four players with four adventurers each (up to 16 adventurers total!) can battle in the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event, which begins <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1546236000"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>In this event, you can take on event-specific quests to defeat the light-element raid boss and earn rewards.</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/31790c9453ccbeb3ffd79cf78bcfcad5.png"></div><div>The new year is almost upon the Halidom! A group of people bringing blessings for the new year in samurai attire arrive from Hinomoto, a land to the east. But when a naginata-wielding young woman who was following that group shows up, the Halidom is thrown into an uproar! Will they all be able to safely ring in the new year?</div><div><br></div><div>If you increase your Friendship with Botan, a character who appears in the event, you&#39;ll be able to officially add her to your group of adventurers!</div><div><br></div><div>Use blazons and emblems collected during the event to get the dragon Shishimai and the Luck of the Draw wyrmprint!</div><div><br></div><div>The main additions and changes from the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event are described below.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Additions:</strong></div><div><strong>[Boss Battles]</strong></div><div>・Kagami mochi will appear on the boss battle map in addition to the regular treasure chests.</div><div>・Kagami mochi have a small chace of dropping a summon ticket.</div><div><strong>[Raid Battles]</strong></div><div>・Each demolished raid boss part has a small chance of dropping a summon ticket.</div><div>・It also has a very small chance of dropping a damascus crystal or a golden fragment.</div><div>・It also has an extremely small chance of dropping a damascus ingot or a golden key.</div><div>(New Year&#39;s gifts will appear a maximum of two times)</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Changes:</strong></div><div>・ There&#39;s an even more extensive event story than the last raid event, Resplendent Refrain.</div><div>・ The appearance rate of the extra raid battle has been adjusted since the last raid event, Resplendent Refrain, to make it appear more frequently.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Event period:</strong></div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1546236000"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1547099999"></span></div><div><br></div><div>Note: If the event ends while you are in a battle, the battle will continue until the results are determined. You will be able to gain rewards according to the results of the battle.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Period for accepting rewards:</strong></div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1546236000"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1547704799"></span></div><div><br></div><div>Note: You&#39;ll be able to perform blazon summons and accept emblem rewards between these times.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Temporary characters:</strong></div><div>Friendship with temporary characters in your party increases when you complete quests. If you achieve maximum friendship during the event, the character will remain with you after the event ends. If a character joins your group for good, you will be able to include them in your party even after the event has ended. The temporary character&#39;s level, stats, equipment, and position in your party will be maintained.</div><div><br></div><div>Note: Even if an event adventurer isn&#39;t permanently added to your collection, any items used to upgrade their level, unlock their Mana Circle, and promote them will not be returned.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Raid battles:</strong></div><div>Raid battles are co-op battles where up to four players can use four adventurers each, bringing up to 16 characters to challenge a raid boss. There are three difficulty levels for raid battles: Beginner, Standard, and Expert. To participate in a raid battle, you must either create a room as the host, or join a room as a guest.</div><div><br></div><div>・ For Hosts:</div><div>Creating a room requires otherworld fragments and stamina. You can obtain otherworld fragments from boss battles.</div><div><br></div><div>・ For Guests:</div><div>Otherworld fragments are not required to participate in Co-op Play. Getherwings will be used. To challenge raid battles, you must be capable of challenging the same difficulty as the Host.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Extra raid battles:</strong></div><div>After clearing a raid battle on expert difficulty, there&#39;s a chance that an Extra Raid Battle will become available. The extra raid battle will disappear once cleared. By fulfilling certain conditions, this quest will continue to appear.</div><div><br></div><div>・ For Hosts:</div><div>Creating a room does not require stamina, getherwings, or otherworld fragments.</div><div><br></div><div>・ For Guests:</div><div>No stamina, getherwings, or otherworld fragments will be expended. Players can only take part while the extra battle appears for them. The extra battle will disappear once players have cleared it as a guest.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Blazon summons:</strong></div><div>Clear boss battles and raid battles to obtain peregrine blazons.</div><div><br></div><div>You can use the blazons you collected for the event&#39;s blazon summoning to get event-specific 5★ dragons, 4★ wyrmprints, and other rewards.</div><div><br></div><div>If you receive the dragon Shishimai as a reward, you can reset the summoning contents. For your 5th reset and afterward, you must have received all rewards to reset the summoning contents.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Emblems:</strong></div><div>You can get rewards such as items and event-specific wyrmprints based on the total number of emblems you gathered during the event.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>■ Event quests:</strong></div><div>You can challenge these quests during the event. There are two types of event quests: Daily and Limited.</div><div><br></div><div>■ Notes:</div><div>1. During raid battles, you will only recover 1/4 of the amount of HP from certain skills and abilities.</div><div>2. You must clear Ch. 2 / 2-1 (Normal) to participate in event quests.</div><div>3. You must clear Ch. 2 / 2-1 (Normal) to participate in Co-op Play.</div><div>4. If you do not reach maximum friendship with temporary characters during the event, they will not join you after the event ends, regardless of their level or stats.</div><div>5. Once the temporary character formally joins your party, you will be able to read their adventurer story.</div><div>6. The boss and raid boss for this event have different stats and skills from the adventurer and dragon you can obtain in the summon showcase or as event rewards.</div><div>7. You will not be able to use blazons, emblems, or otherworld fragments obtained in this event in future events.</div><div>8. For details concerning this raid event, check the Help section on the raid event&rsquo;s top page in the game.</div><div>9. The event schedule and content may change without warning.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing the Dragalia Lost game!</div>,start_time:1546236000,update_time1547100007